---
import CloudinaryImage from './CloudinaryImage.astro';
---

<section class="py-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-green-50">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">

      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
          Protecting Your Drain Field: The Unsung Hero of Septic Health
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          When it comes to your septic system, the drain field is often overlooked—but it's absolutely essential for keeping everything functioning properly. The drain field, sometimes called the leach field, is where wastewater from your septic tank is filtered and safely returned to the environment.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center mb-16">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Why Drain Field Maintenance Matters</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Your drain field is the final stop for wastewater in your septic system, and keeping it in top shape is crucial. When solid waste or biofilm buildup clogs the drain field, it can cause backups, strong odors, and even contamination of your local groundwater system.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            These problems are not only expensive to fix—they can also pose serious health risks. Regular maintenance, including the use of a USDA Certified Biobased Product like Pour the PORT, helps break down solid waste and prevents biofilm buildup, keeping your drain field clear and your septic system running smoothly.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-6 mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-yellow-800 mb-2">⚠️ Warning Signs of Drain Field Trouble</h4>
            <ul class="text-yellow-700 space-y-2">
              <li>• Soggy or standing water over the drain field</li>
              <li>• Strong sewage odors in your yard</li>
              <li>• Extremely lush, green grass over the drain field</li>
              <li>• Slow drains throughout your home</li>
              <li>• Sewage backups into your house</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center">
          <CloudinaryImage
            publicId="pour-the-port/septic-drain-field-diagram"
            alt="Septic drain field protection and maintenance diagram"
            width={600}
            height={400}
            loading="lazy"
            class="rounded-lg shadow-lg mb-6"
          />
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 italic">
            Healthy drain field with proper bacterial balance and waste breakdown
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8 mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 text-center">
          How Pour the PORT Supports Drain Field Longevity
        </h3>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="bg-green-100 rounded-full w-20 h-20 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
              <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-green-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Breaks Down Solid Waste</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Natural bacteria cultures work continuously to decompose waste, preventing solids from clogging your drain field pipes.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="bg-blue-100 rounded-full w-20 h-20 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
              <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Eliminates Biofilm Buildup</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Organic acids break surface tension and eliminate biofilm that can clog drain field distribution boxes and pipes.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="bg-purple-100 rounded-full w-20 h-20 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
              <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-purple-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4.318 6.318a4.5 4.5 0 000 6.364L12 20.364l7.682-7.682a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364-6.364L12 7.636l-1.318-1.318a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364 0z"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Maintains Beneficial Microbes</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Regular applications maintain optimal bacterial levels, creating a healthy ecosystem throughout your entire septic system.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-600 text-white rounded-lg p-8 text-center">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Simple Steps for Ongoing Drain Field Care</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
          <div>
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">1</div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Apply Pour the PORT</h4>
            <p class="text-green-100">3 times per year to maintain bacterial balance</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">2</div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Protect the Area</h4>
            <p class="text-green-100">Keep vehicles and heavy equipment off the drain field</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">3</div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Monitor Performance</h4>
            <p class="text-green-100">Watch for warning signs and address issues early</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-xl mb-6">
          <strong>Pour the PORT is more than just a septic tank treatment—it's a complete solution for your entire septic system.</strong>
        </p>

        <a
          href="#pricing"
          class="bg-white text-green-600 hover:bg-gray-100 font-bold py-4 px-8 rounded-full text-lg transition-all duration-300 transform hover:scale-105 shadow-lg inline-flex items-center"
        >
          Protect Your Drain Field Today
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"></path>
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>